_refine_special_details          
;
The iodine atoms within the Sn-I layer were refined as disordered 
over each two sets of positions related to each other by 
pseudo-monoclinic symmetry (see below). ADPs of atom pairs from the 
major and minor moiety were each constrained to be identical. 
Subject to these conditions the occupancy ratios refined to 0.9873(10) 
to 0.0127(10) and to 0.9869(10) to 0.0131(10) in the two Sn-I layers, 
respectively. Associated disorder of the ammonium nitrogen atoms was 
not resolved and was omitted from the refinement. 

The structure exhibits monoclinic C-centered pseudo-symmetry and is 
twinned by a symmetry element of this setting by a rotation around 
the reciprocal axis (-1 1 0). Refinement against the twin 
transformation matrix 0 -1 0, -1 0 0, 0 0 -1 yielded a twin ratio of 
0.8054(5) to 0.1946(5). Exact C-centered symmetry is broken by the 
close to perfect ordering of the iodine atoms within the Sn-I layers 
and the ammonium nitrogen atoms. 1:1 disorder would have resulted in 
monoclinic C-centered symmetry. 
;
